icide of his girlfriend.\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/57069 |title=Mohabbatein |accessdate=7 July 2014 |author=Adarsh, Taran |date=15 December 2000 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140520143737/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/57069 |archivedate=20 May 2014 }}</ref>\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Mere Yaar Ki Shaadi Hai]]''\n| 2002\n| {{sortname|Sanjay|Gadhvi}}\n| [[Uday Chopra]], [[Tulip Joshi]], [[Jimmy Shergill]], [[Bipasha Basu]]\n| A man decides to break the engagement of his childhood friend after realising that he is in love with her.\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/jun/07mere.htm |title=Meet Bollywood's Julia Roberts and Meg Ryan |accessdate=27 December 2014 |author=Verma, Sukanya |date=7 June 2002 |publisher=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924141726/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/jun/07mere.htm |archivedate=24 September 2015 }}</ref>\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Mujhse Dosti Karoge!]]''\n| 2002\n| {{sortname|Kunal|Kohli}}\n| [[Hrithik Roshan]], [[Rani Mukerji]], [[Kareena Kapoor]], [[Uday Chopra]]\n| Raj and Tina fall in love while corresponding through e-mails. After Raj proposes to Tina he realises that the e-mails were written by Tina's friend, Pooja.\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/aug/09dosti.htm |title=Why Hrithik is a heartthrob! |accessdate=27 December 2014 |author=Verma, Sukanya |date=9 August 2002 |publisher=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721014516/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/aug/09dosti.htm |archivedate=21 July 2015 }}</ref>\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Saathiya (film)|Saathiya]]''\n| 2002\n| {{sortname|Shaad|Ali}}\n| [[Rani Mukerji]], [[Vivek Oberoi]]\n| A couple face a series of troubles and misunderstandings after they elope and marry.\n| <ref>{{cite news|author=Jhunjhunwala, Udita|title=Saathiya |work=[[Mid Day]]|date=21 December 2002|url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/hindimoviesreview/2002/december/39633.htm|accessdate=26 October 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20030202113210/http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/hindimoviesreview/2002/december/39633.htm|archivedate=2 February 2003}}</ref>\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Hum Tum]]''\n| 2004\n| {{sortname|Kunal|Kohli|nolink=yes}}\n| [[Saif Ali Khan]], [[Rani Mukerji]], [[Rishi Kapoor]]\n| Karan and Rhea casually encounter each other at various stages of their lives and eventually fall in love after the death of Rhea's husband.\n|<ref>{{cite news|last=Mahesh |first=Chitra |work=The Hindu |title=Hum Tum |date=4 June 2004 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/06/04/stories/2004060401780300.htm |accessdate=25 January 2008 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040912105133/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/06/04/stories/2004060401780300.htm |archivedate=12 September 2004 }}</ref>\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Dhoom]]''\n| 2004\n| {{sortname|Sanjay|Gadhvi|nolink=yes}}\n| [[Abhishek Bachchan]], [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]], [[Uday Chopra]], [[Esha Deol]], [[Rimi Sen]]\n| A police officer and a motorbike dealer team up to stop a group of bank robbers.\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Dhoom : Movie Review |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/65066 |date=27 August 2004 |first=Taran |last=Adarsh |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=6 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202235816/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/65066 |archivedate= 2 December 2013 }}</ref>\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Veer-Zaara]]''\n| 2004\n| {{sortname|Yash|Chopra|nolink=yes}}\n| [[Shah Rukh Khan]], [[Preity Zinta]], [[Rani Mukerji]]\n| An Indian Air Force pilot falls in love with a Pakistani woman. Misunderstandings lead to his imprisonment for 22 years and a Pakistani lawyer fights for his rights.\n| <ref name=\