ohit |title='Aurangzeb' review: The cruel persuasion of money and power |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aurangzeb-review-the-cruel-persuasion-of-money-and-power/392232-47-77.html |publisher=CNN-IBN |date=17 May 2013 |accessdate=21 April 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131226162951/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aurangzeb-review-the-cruel-persuasion-of-money-and-power/392232-47-77.html |archivedate=26 December 2013 }}</ref>\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Shuddh Desi Romance]]''\n| 2013\n| {{sortname|Maneesh|Sharma|nolink=yes}}\n| [[Sushant Singh Rajput]], [[Parineeti Chopra]], [[Vaani Kapoor]], [[Rishi Kapoor]]\n| Raghu runs away from his arranged wedding to Tara and begins cohabiting with Gayatri. On the day of his marriage to her, Gayatri runs out on him too.\n|<ref>{{cite web|title='Shuddh Desi Romance' review: It's a non-formulaic, charming little film |url=http://ibnlive.com/news/shuddh-desi-romance-review-its-a-nonformulaic-charming-little-film/420141-47-84.html|author=Masand, Rajeev|publisher=CNN-IBN|date=7 September 2013|accessdate=9 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Dhoom 3]]''{{efn|name=dhoom3|Dubbed versions in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] were also released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-box-office-dhoom-3-is-a-blockbuster/20131223.htm |title=Box Office: Dhoom 3 is a blockbuster! |accessdate=31 December 2014 |publisher=Rediff.com |date=23 December 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030164851/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-box-office-dhoom-3-is-a-blockbuster/20131223.htm |archivedate=30 October 2014 }}</ref>}}\n| 2013\n| {{sortname|Vijay Krishna|Acharya}}\n| [[Aamir Khan]], [[Abhishek Bachchan]], [[Katrina Kaif]], [[Uday Chopra]], [[Jackie Shroff]]\n| A circus boy, trained in circus theatrics, vows to take down a corrupt Chicago-based bank after his father's suicide. Two police officers from Mumbai try to catch them.\n| <ref>{{cite web|last=Chopra |first=Sonia |title=Dhoom 3 review: The great Indian circus, indeed! |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/dhoom-3-review-the-great-indian-circus-indeed-review-bollywood-15045625.html |publisher=[[Sify]] |date=20 December 2013 |accessdate=4 December 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140618101953/http://www.sify.com/movies/dhoom-3-review-the-great-indian-circus-indeed-review-bollywood-15045625.html |archivedate=18 June 2014 }}</ref>\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Gunday]]''{{efn|name=gunday|A dubbed version in [[Bengali language|Bengali]] was also released.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bhaskaran |first=Gautaman |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/why-gunday-has-created-panic-in-bengal/article1-1183859.aspx |title=Why Gunday has created panic in Bengal? |accessdate=31 December 2014 |work=Hindustan Times |date=14 February 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141231135249/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/why-gunday-has-created-panic-in-bengal/article1-1183859.aspx |archivedate=31 December 2014 }}</ref>}}\n| 2014\n| {{sortname|Ali Abbas|Zafar|nolink=yes}}\n| [[Ranveer Singh]], [[Arjun Kapoor]], [[Priyanka Chopra]], [[Irrfan Khan]]\n| Two refugees from Bangladesh emerge as the most powerful coal bandits in [[Calcutta]]. Misunderstandings arise when they both fall in love with the same [[cabaret]] dancer.\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/gunday-review-starring-priyanka-chopra-ranveer-singh-arjun-kapoor/1/343438.html |title=Movie review: Gunday is old wine in a new bottle, it tastes awesome! |author=Khilnani, Rohit |work=[[India Today]] |date=14 February 2014 |accessdate=25 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224223702/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/gunday-review-starring-priyanka-chopra-ranveer-singh-arjun-kapoor/1/343438.html |archivedate=24 February 2014 }}</ref>\n\n|