ive.org/web/20140901143559/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/201895 |archivedate= 1 September 2014 }}</ref><br /><ref>{{cite news|author=Us Salam, Ziya |work=[[The Hindu]] |url=http://www.thehindujobs.com/thehindu/fr/2001/12/21/stories/2001122100840203.htm |title=Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham |accessdate=14 February 2011 |date=21 December 2001 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100205104008/http://thehindujobs.com/thehindu/fr/2001/12/21/stories/2001122100840203.htm |archivedate= 5 February 2010 }}</ref>\n|-\n\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Kal Ho Naa Ho]]''\n|2003\n|{{sortname|Nikhil|Advani}}\n| {{sortname|Yash|Johar}},<br />[[Karan Johar]]\n|[[Jaya Bachchan]], [[Shah Rukh Khan]], [[Saif Ali Khan]], [[Preity Zinta]]\n| A man with a fatal heart disease tries to play matchmaker to a troubled young woman and her best friend, despite being in love with her.\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Kal Ho Naa Ho (2003) |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/201866 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=20 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141225130721/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/201866 |archivedate=25 December 2014 }}</ref><br /><ref>{{cite book|editor1=Meuff, Russell |editor2=Raphael, Raphael |title=Transnational Stardom: International Celebrity in Film and Popular Culture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i682iHvv_c4C&pg=PA214|date=21 February 2013|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|isbn=978-1-137-26828-0|page=214}}</ref>\n|-\n\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Kaal (2005 film)|Kaal]]''{{efn|name=red|The film was co-produced with [[Red Chillies Entertainment]].<ref name=\"kaal\"/><ref name=\"student\"/>}}\n|2005\n|{{sortname|Soham|Shah|nolink=yes}}\n|{{sortname|Karan|Johar}},<br />[[Shah Rukh Khan]]\n|[[Ajay Devgn]], [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]], [[Vivek Oberoi]], [[Esha Deol]], [[Lara Dutta]]\n| A group of tourists in a national park are traumatised by an unexplained force, and they