a Roy Kapur]], [[Kalki Koechlin]]\n| A man and a woman of contrasting personalities fall in love during the course of a common friend's wedding.\n|<ref name=\"jawaani\">{{cite web|title=Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani (2013) |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/547969 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=20 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150113015044/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/547969 |archivedate=13 January 2015 }}</ref><br /><ref>{{cite web|last=Sen |first=Raja |title=Review: Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani disappoints |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-disappoints/20130531.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=31 May 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130606072818/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-disappoints/20130531.htm |archivedate= 6 June 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n\n! scope=\"row\" | ''{{sort|Lunchbox|[[The Lunchbox]]}}''{{efn|name=lunch|The film was co-produced with UTV Motion Pictures, [[DAR Motion Pictures]] and [[Sikhya Entertainment]].<ref name=\"lunch\"/>}}\n|2013\n|{{sortname|Ritesh|Batra}}\n|{{sortname|Guneet|Monga}},<br />[[Anurag Kashyap]],<br />Arun Rangachari\n|[[Irrfan Khan]], [[Nimrat Kaur]], [[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]]\n| An unhappy housewife and a lonely widower correspond through letters in hope of a better future with each other.\n|<ref name=\"lunch\">{{cite web|title=The Lunchbox (2013) |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/588497 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=20 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150120115150/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/588497 |archivedate=20 January 2015 }}</ref><br /><ref>{{cite news|last=Weissberg |first=Jay |url=https://variety.com/2013/film/reviews/cannes-film-review-the-lunchbox-1200483926/ |title=Cannes Film Review: 'The Lunchbox' |work=Variety |date=19 May 2013 |accessdat