ed attraction towards a woman, but she is intent on keeping the relationship platonic.\n|<ref>{{cite news|title=Anushka Sharma begins shooting \u2018Ae Dil Hai Mushkil\u2019 |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/anushka-sharma-begins-shooting-ae-dil-hai-mushkil/ |date=9 September 2015 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=9 September 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150911001824/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/anushka-sharma-begins-shooting-ae-dil-hai-mushkil/ |archivedate=11 September 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Dear Zindagi]]''{{efn|name=zindagi|The film was co-produced with [[Red Chillies Entertainment]] and Hope Productions.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dear Zindagi (2016) |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/7991087 |date=19 July 2016 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=21 July 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160722042124/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/7991087 |archivedate=22 July 2016 }}</ref>}}\n|2016\n|{{sortname|Gauri|Shinde}}\n| {{sortname|Karan|Johar}}<br />[[Gauri Khan]],<br /> [[R. Balki]]\n| [[Alia Bhatt]], [[Shah Rukh Khan]]\n| A therapist helps a troubled cinematographer resolve conflicts with her parents.\n|<ref>{{cite news|title=Dear Zindagi review: Shah Rukh Khan hops on the 'gyan' bandwagon yet charms with his presence |url=http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/dear-zindagi-review-shah-rukh-khan-hops-on-the-gyan-bandwagon-yet-charms-with-his-presence-3125830.html |last=Gauri |first=Gayatri |date=26 November 2016 |work=Firstpost |accessdate=21 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220222525/http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/dear-zindagi-review-shah-rukh-khan-hops-on-the-gyan-bandwagon-yet-charms-with-his-presence-3125830.html |archivedate=20 December 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Ok Jaanu]]''{{efn|name=jaanu|The film was co-produced with [[Ma